-- Aer Lingus Pension Deficit Can’t Delay Sale, Minister Tells Post
-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 2012-05-13T12:29:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-13/aer-lingus-pension-deficit-can-t-delay-sale-minister-tells-post.html
The Irish government’s sale of its 25
percent stake in Aer Lingus Group Plc won’t be delayed
indefinitely because of the company’s 700 million-euro ($904
million) pension deficit, Ireland’s transport Minister  Leo Varadkar  told the Sunday Business Post.  To contact the reporter on this story:
